for the tuition for the private school, so I was tested and received a full scholarship.   Now, I am married to a public school assistant principal.  We live in the best public school system in the metro area and send all three (3) of our children to that public school.   That old public school that was so dangerous 30 years ago? Well, it was closed down for the very reasons my parents refused to send me there.   Allison Benedikt makes an interesting argument, but it is hardly universal.  Change takes time -- by the time a parent might make a difference in the local public school system, their child would have graduated.   My private school education served me very well, and I am truly thankful I did not have to go to school at John Marshall!!! And, why are we focusing on the Private Schools when there is absolutely no mention of Home Schooling? "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="1152" language="en" documentId="3824" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="FL_RED62" date="Aug 29, 2013 6:29PM" docType="artcomment" origUrl="http://living.msn.com/family-parenting/the-family-room-blog-post?post=ab228ffc-1e99-4b37-a7b8-0b6a4c3fb240" topic="public-private-schools" thumbsUp="3" thumbsDown="0" origId="3824" notes="" title="Is it wrong to send kids to private school?"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="1152"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39"/></xmi:XMI>